
[1]impenitency

   IMPEN'ITENCY, n. [L. in and poenitens, from poeniteo, to repent, poena,
   pain.] Want of penitence or repentance; absence of contrition or sorrow
   for sin; obduracy; hardness of heart. Final impenitence dooms the
   sinner to inevitable punishment.

   He will advance from one degree of impenitence to another.
